 and (2) both the fruit-eating C. perspicillata and the flower-feeding G. soricina were significantly more reliant on spatial cues than associated sensory cues for relocating food.\nConclusions/Significance: These findings, taken together with past results, provide evidence of a powerful, experienceindependent predilection of both species to rely on spatial cues when attempting to relocate food.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Carter, Gerald G.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Ratcliffe, John M.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Galef, Bennett G.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Arlettaz, Rapha\u00ebl", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/7b83eee54a98848b346da88a1e0d62d9", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/6528f6cc7fd07e66fcabb2f57222eb81832f061cb226fe7980801ae645962aa3", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/6RUEQJQC", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/6RUEQJQC", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/6e7d492bce5736586d4f96caf6a3a1e5!/b87950-90413", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/330417efcaa2560c9b8ebcd6fae17ce0", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "custom": {"dwc:class": ["Mammalia"], "dwc:kingdom": ["Animalia"], "dwc:order": ["Chiroptera"], "dwc:phylum": ["Chordata"]}, "resource_type": {"title": "Journal article", "type": "publication", "subtype": "article"}, "journal": {"issue": "5", "pages": "e10808", "title": "PLoS ONE", "volume": "5"}, "alternate_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/7b83eee54a98848b346da88a1e0d62d